    "Tony W. Cartledge": ").\nDavid `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s Dilemma, 28:1-2\nDavid `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s plan proceeded perfectly until Achish did the one thing\nDavid `[char_David_Rut_4]` could not afford for him to do: he laid plans to attack Israel,\nincorporating David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s band into the Philistine forces. It appears\nthat David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s show of allegiance to Achish had been too convincing.\nThe conversation between the two reveals that David `[char_David_Rut_4]` was still\nthinking on his feet, though now in danger of a major gaffe. When\nAchish said \u201cYou know, of course, that you and your men are to go\nout with me in the army\u201d ("
